PRIVACY POLICY

App: GIF Maker, Video to GIF
Developer: [Your Name / Company Name]
Effective date: [e.g., May 30, 2026]

Thank you for using GIF Maker, Video to GIF ("the App"). This Privacy Policy
explains how the App handles your information. The App processes your photos and
videos on your device to create GIFs. We do not require an account, and we do not
collect your media files. The App shows advertisements, which involve limited data
collection by our advertising partner as described below.

1. INFORMATION WE COLLECT
We (the developer) do not collect or store your personal content (photos, videos,
or GIFs) on any server. We do not have user accounts and do not ask you to sign in.

Your media content is processed ONLY on your device, solely to provide the App's
features:
- Photos and videos you choose to import, to create or edit GIFs.
- Camera input you record, to create a GIF from the camera.
- GIF files you open or create, to edit, convert, or export them.
This content is never uploaded to us.

2. ADVERTISING
The App displays ads through Google AdMob, provided by Google LLC. To show ads,
AdMob may collect and process certain data, which may include:
- Advertising ID (a resettable device identifier)
- Approximate (non-precise) location derived from IP address
- Device information and ad-interaction data (for ad delivery, frequency capping,
  measurement, and fraud prevention)

This data is collected and used by Google in accordance with Google's policies.
For details on how Google uses this data, see:
- Google Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
- How Google uses information from sites or apps that use its services:
  https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites

You can reset or limit ad personalization using your device's advertising settings
(Settings > Google > Ads), or opt out of ad personalization there.

If you are in the EEA/UK, the App requests your consent for personalized ads where
required by law before such ads are shown. You may change your choice at any time.

3. HOW YOUR CONTENT IS STORED
- Files you select are used only to perform the action you request.
- GIFs, videos, and frames you create are saved to your device's storage/gallery
  so you can access and share them. These files stay on your device.

4. PERMISSIONS WE USE AND WHY
- Photos and media (READ_MEDIA_IMAGES, READ_MEDIA_VIDEO / storage on older
  Android): to pick photos, videos, and GIFs, and to save your creations.
- Camera (CAMERA): to record video and turn it into a GIF, only while recording.
- Internet (INTERNET, ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE) and Advertising ID (AD_ID): to load
  and display ads.
You can grant or revoke permissions at any time in your device Settings.

5. SHARING YOUR CREATIONS
When you share a GIF or video, you choose another app (e.g., WhatsApp, Instagram,
Messenger) using your device's standard share feature. Content shared that way is
handled by the app you choose, under that app's own privacy policy. The App itself
does not upload your files.

6. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES
The App uses Google AdMob for advertising (see Section 2). We do not sell your
personal information. Other than the ad services described above, the App does not
send your data to third parties.

7. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
The App is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal
information from children.

8. DATA SECURITY
Your media content stays on your device and is not transmitted to us. Ad-related
data is handled by Google under its security and privacy practices.

9. YOUR CHOICES
- Reset/limit your Advertising ID: device Settings > Google > Ads.
- Manage app permissions: device Settings > Apps > GIF Maker, Video to GIF.
- (EEA/UK) Change ad-consent choices in the App's consent dialog.

10. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this
page with an updated effective date.

